	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A Game Boy Color flash card should work in a Game Boy, Super Game Boy, Game Boy Pocket, Game Boy Color, Game Boy Advance, Game Boy Advance SP, or Game Boy Player. But by the time I got into GBA development (November 2001), GBC flash cards were already hard to find.
<br />
<br />A GBA flash card such as the FireLinker or SuperCard should work in a GBA, GBA SP, GB Player, GB micro, DS, or DS Lite. To use GB or GBC software on a GBA flash card, you use the "Goomba Color" emulator. It's not an entirely accurate emulation due to the GBA's limitations, but it is still Running On Real Nintendo Hardware.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


